title: For Sale:  1950's Browning FN Herstal
postcontent: Up for sale a FN Herstal Browning "Trombone" Slide Action Carbine Rifle. The quality of the parts, the fit and finish and the silky-smooth action belie how much it must have cost to produce the Trombone. When you cycle the action, you can feel the engineering / manufacturing build quality. It locks shut with authority, it ejects with aplomb, the forearm moves like it's on ball bearings. She feels like a Swiss watch. It is certainly one of the most desired rifles in her class and has a following like few others. She comes to your shoulder like it was meant to be there. It is deceptively petite, but shoots the lights out. The re-blued finish is in excellent condition and the round knob blond walnut stock is in very nice condition showing only slight wear from handling and storage. There is a small mark under the rear stock, but overall the blonde walnut glows in the sun showing rich wood grain and texture. She comes with the sporting sight in the rear and a dove tail up front. The rifle also features an 11 round tubular feed system and a 22" round barrel. The pump handle is grooved and provides plenty of positive traction up forward.
